➜Chrysanthemum enters harvest in N China's Hebei
http://www.sohu.com/a/433707574_162758	21933
<p><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/q_70/images03/20201123/dbd1bca771db45a8b136fb3a461604a1.jpeg" /></p>
<p>Photo taken on Nov. 20, 2020 shows that farmers were picking edible chrysanthemums at a greenhouse in Taer Village, Xuanhua District, Zhangjiakou City, north China's Hebei Province. As chrysanthemums Taer Village entered the harvest season, farmers were busy picking, drying and processing the fresh flowers. (Chen Xiaodong/Guangming Picture)</p>
